; Regression test for issue #1604: Every N days problem in budgeting (BZ#532)
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/1604
;
; Bug: 'every N weeks from [date]' did not honor the start date for
; subsequent occurrences. Instead it aligned to week boundaries, causing
; the second budget entry to appear too early (e.g. Mar 7 instead of
; Mar 15 for "every 2 weeks from 2010/03/01").

~ every 2 weeks from 2010/03/01
    Expenses:Bills        $100.00
    Assets:Checking

test reg --budget --now=2010/04/01
10-Mar-01 Budget transaction    Expenses:Bills             $-100.00     $-100.00
10-Mar-01 Budget transaction    Assets:Checking             $100.00            0
10-Mar-15 Budget transaction    Expenses:Bills             $-100.00     $-100.00
10-Mar-15 Budget transaction    Assets:Checking             $100.00            0
10-Mar-29 Budget transaction    Expenses:Bills             $-100.00     $-100.00
10-Mar-29 Budget transaction    Assets:Checking             $100.00            0
end test
